name: Release 2.3.0
body: **NB**: We identified an issue in this release that can corrupt the database when an `UPDATE` statement is stored within a function. We released `v2.3.1` to address this. If you defined functions with `UPDATE` statements in `v2.3.0` please kindly remove those function definitions, upgrade to `v2.3.1` and then add them back.

name: Release v1.0.1
body:
- Adds a patch for [GHSA-x5fr-7hhj-34j3](https://github.com/surrealdb/surrealdb/security/advisories/GHSA-x5fr-7hhj-34j3).
  - Tables defined without explicit permissions have `NONE` instead of `FULL` permissions.
  - Table permissions are always explicitly displayed with the `INFO FOR DB` statement.
